        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/554513464?book_show_action=true">Mar 06, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jadey" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jadey" href="/user/show/16832706-jadey">Jadey</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781481972994" href="/book/show/17283555-to-stand-beside-her">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer554513464" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13637684789014325106">I was given the oppertunity to read this book in return for an honest review. After reading the blurb I knew it was something that, I wouldnt normally read but still thought the story sounded interesting and was happy to give it a chance.<br/><br/>Im glad that i did! I thoroughly enjoyed this book and found all of the main characters intruiging. After a couple of chapters in i was excited to see where the story was headed. <br/>In fact i found it hard to put this book down :)<br/><br/>Leila was a strong and highly likea</span>
  <span id="freeText13637684789014325106" style="display:none">I was given the oppertunity to read this book in return for an honest review. After reading the blurb I knew it was something that, I wouldnt normally read but still thought the story sounded interesting and was happy to give it a chance.<br /><br />Im glad that i did! I thoroughly enjoyed this book and found all of the main characters intruiging. After a couple of chapters in i was excited to see where the story was headed. <br />In fact i found it hard to put this book down :)<br /><br />Leila was a strong and highly likeable character and it was nice to see her relationships develop with both the king and Anatolio. <br /><br />If i had any qualms regarding this book it would be the ending... It happened so quickly. I was shocked it stopped where it did. That said, it could easily follow into a second book if the author chose to do so. <br /><br />All in all a great read that i would recommend to my friends. Im glad i took a break from the norm and gave this book a try :)</span>
